What you need to know:

Otieno inched closer to qualifying for the Tokyo Olympic Games in 100m when he improved his personal record by 0.3 seconds, missing the Olympics qualifying time by 0.06secOtieno, who had clocked 10.19sec to win his 100m semi-final race, stormed to victory in 10.11sec in the final on SaturdayThe qualifying standard for Tokyo Olympic Games is 10.05sec in 100m and 20.24 sec in 200m